reviewText: I like viewing older B and Ws. I also like the "corny" scripts. No deep drama like most of today's overrated movies. Actors/Actresses played their roles w/o profanity but with open imagination.
I lived roy rogers when I was a kid and it has not changed,i still love em

The only thing good about this movie is the title and the fact that it's a Roy Rogers movie.  The Son's of the Pioneer's are always great as well.  I love old movies, but try as I might, I just couldn't make it to the end.  I would rather watch "Rio Bravo."  But that's just me.

Roy Rogers and Dale Evans are impossibly young in this 1944 flick...I'd forgotten what a sensational voice he had. Even Gabby Hayes is a young middle age and still singing with the Sons of the Pioneers. It's no wonder I love Mexican trios music...it sounds just like the songs in this movie.  Fun, nostalgic piece.
